India Today - 6 October 2014
English | PDF | 192 pages | 24.6 mb

India Today is an Indian weekly magazine of current affairs. 

INTERVIEW - CJI R.M. LODHA 38
"Those Talking of Corruption in the Judiciary Are Themselves Corrupt"
CJI talks about the judiciary and its frayed relationship with the executive.

A Date with Joy 62
A new movement to create a national week of giving is growing across India. Block your calender and be happy.

Steady in the Long Run 49
Savings are fine but insurance is a must for future crises.

THE BIG STORY - MAKE IN INDIA
Make It Happen 22
While Narendra Modi invites the world to do business here, the onus is on him to cut through the regulatory rubble and make India a manufacturing hub

NEIGHBOURS - CHINA 
The Thin Redline 44
The standoffs along the LAC could be China's attempt at forcing India into an early resolution to the border dispute.
